# Senior / Lead Software Engineer - ClusterHQ

Your challenge

This is your chance to be part of something new, where you can have a voice and be recognised for defining and building disruptive cloud technology. Containers will impact infrastructure, application architecture and software delivery as fundamentally in the coming years as virtualization has in the last decade. 

You can lead on, or contribute to, product and technical architecture, software design, implementation, and mentoring and pairing with less experienced engineers.

We code in Python and Go using asynchronous frameworks, and you can transfer from another language. It’s TDD and pair programming in small SCRUM teams, enjoying easy knowledge share with your colleagues in development, devops and quality assurance.

ClusterHQ is offering relocation to Bristol, UK, which is fast becoming the cloud computing hub of Europe and is renowned for its high quality of life.

About you

- You’re ready for a progressive job as a Senior Engineer, Technical Lead or Architect
- You can build and maintain high quality, fault tolerant, scalable distributed software systems 
- You’re skilled in event-driven asynchronous programming 
- You bring knowledge of domains such as: networking, cloud, clustering, virtualization, storage, middleware, OS development, orchestration, micro services, containers etc.
- You have advanced coding skills, using languages such as: C/C++ | Erlang | Fortran | Golang | Haskell | Java | Python | Scala | Ruby | etc.
- You may have encountered technologies such as: Docker | Kubernetes | CoreOS | Oracle Coherence | Node.JS | Tornado | gevent | Twisted | Tulip | Java Message Server | Java Spaces | asyncio | AKKA | Atmosphere | Autobahn | Apache Camel | Asio | Klein | Netty | OpenVZ etc.
- You work openly and inclusively, and you enjoy code reviews and sharing ideas

Salary and benefits

- Competitive joining salary
- Equity in a fast growing 
- Discretionary relocation assistance
- Flexible working | 28 days holiday + public holidays | pension | death in service | income protection | private healthcare | dental care | Cyclescheme | good coffee | on site restaurant

Located: central Bristol, South West UK; 1:45 to London by train

About us

ClusterHQ is a newly funded open source software provider, front and centre of the containerisation world. With five years in R&D and £12m funding from Accel Partners, we make our first major release of Flocker this summer, supporting the Docker ecosystem. Effective software design is at the heart of our organisation and fundamental to our future. Our global team includes accomplished open source contributors on projects such as Twisted and OpenZFS. We invite you to join our world class engineering teams.
